AppendToFile(Stream, String)

Reads the bytes from the current stream and writes them to the end of a file. Copying begins at the current position in the current stream, and does not reset the position of the current stream after the writing is complete.

Declaration
public static void AppendToFile(this Stream stream, string path)
Parameters

IterBooleanBinarySavableDictPairs<T>(Stream, Boolean)

Iterates System.Boolean-IBinarySavable tuples from the stream. There can be a data checking code and a count in the stream prior to all data pairs. To only read pairs, use IterBooleanBinarySavableTuples<T>(Stream) instead.

Declaration
public static IEnumerator<(bool, T)> IterBooleanBinarySavableDictPairs<T>(this Stream stream, bool validityCheck = false)
    where T : IBinarySavable, new()
Parameters
Type Name Description
System.IO.Stream stream

The stream to read from.
System.Boolean validityCheck

true if a 8-byte code is read from the stream before all actual data. If this code is not the expected value, then the data in the stream is corrupted.
Returns
Type Description
System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator<System.ValueTuple<System.Boolean, T>>

Declaration
public static void ReadDict(this Stream stream, IDictionary<short, long> outputDict, bool validityCheck = false)
Parameters
Type Name Description
System.IO.Stream stream

The stream to read from.
System.Collections.Generic.IDictionary<System.Int16, System.Int64> outputDict

The key-value pairs read from the stream are added to this dictionary.
System.Boolean validityCheck

true if a 8-byte code is read from the stream before all actual data. If this code is not the expected value, then the data in the stream is corrupted.
| Improve this Doc View Source

Parameters
Type Name Description
System.IO.Stream stream

The stream to read from.

true if a 8-byte code is written to the stream before all actual data. When the dictionary is later read from the stream, this code should be at the reading start position, or otherwise the data in the stream is corrupted.

System.Boolean validityCheck

true if a 8-byte code is written to the stream before all actual data. When the dictionary is later read from the stream, this code should be at the reading start position, or otherwise the data in the stream is corrupted.

true if a 8-byte code is written to the stream before all actual data. When the dictionary is later read from the stream, this code should be at the reading start position, or otherwise the data in the stream is corrupted.

System.Collections.Generic.IDictionary<System.UInt16, System.SByte> dict

The dictionary object to write to the stream.
System.Boolean validityCheck

true if a 8-byte code is written to the stream before all actual data. When the dictionary is later read from the stream, this code should be at the reading start position, or otherwise the data in the stream is corrupted.
| Improve this Doc View Source

WriteToFile(Stream, String)

Reads the bytes from the current stream and writes them to a file. Copying begins at the current position in the current stream, and does not reset the position of the current stream after the writing is complete. If the file already exists, it will be overwritten.

Declaration
public static void WriteToFile(this Stream stream, string path)
Parameters
Type Name Description
System.IO.Stream stream

A System.IO.Stream.
System.String path

The path of the file to write.

System.Int32 count

The number of integers to be written into the current stream.

!!! Note this number should be no larger than the number of integers from startIndex to the end of the array.
System.Byte[] buffer

A byte array used to temporarily store data to write.
